content.description: Look for a belay anchor at ground level.  Follow the bolts to grade 43 cold shuts with grade 43 chains.  Looks easy from the ground, but what looks like blocky downpulls turns out to be mostly slopers and sidepulls.  Well protected intermediate sport lead.
content.protection: 7 Stainless Steel bolts with SMC hangers.

content.description: First climb on the east end of Lizzy Rock.  Watch for a belay anchor at the base of the climb.  Mixed climb with four visible bolts.  Climb straight towards first bolt, protecting with gear as needed.  Circumvent the first bolt to the right of the hump.  Turn left and up and chase the bolts to the chains.  Crux is around the third bolt.
content.protection: 4 1/2 Stainless steel bolts with Fixe hangers, grade 43 cold shuts and grade 43 chains and small SLCDs

content.description: Left of Humpty dumpty sharing same chains and belay anchor.  Follow 4 bolts with Fixe hangers, to grade 43 cold shuts and grade 43 chains.
content.protection: 4 1/2 Stainless steel bolts with Fixe hangers, grade 43 cold shuts and grade 43 chains.

content.description: South facing crag that is the site of some nice new routes.  A good area for Winter climbing on moderate days.  Great views of the city and some really nice routes.
